ain id="content"><article id="new-article-template"><div class="css-1bfdg3q e1pkqesp0"><div class="css-1qjp74c e8tkvfk0"><div class="css-1r2sn2n e1mdktgm0"><section class="css-qm1vln e1m3q8rc0"><div class="css-b4a1pi elvs37n0"><span class="css-1te5c83 e11l78dl0"><a href="/films/"><span>电影</span></a></span><span class="css-1mdqtqm e11bnqe00">|经济学家现场活动</span></div></section></div><div class="css-1r2sn2n e1mdktgm0"><div class="css-17yzdrv euxoahl0"><section class="css-12k3cm0 e1ey6m751"><div class="css-1746s8a e1ey6m752"><p class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"><span>克雷恩</span><small>的反攻</small>并未按计划进行。截至9月底，泽连斯基总统的军队仅收复了俄罗斯军队6月份占领的领土的0.25%。</p><p class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0"> <i>《经济学人</i>》的编辑们坐下来讨论战争前景，分析美国和北约角色的变化，并思考南半球领导人对这场冲突的反应。我们的专家分享了最近与泽连斯基总统和乌克兰其他高层决策者会面的见解，评估了最新的军事和外交事态发展。</p><p class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0">与赞尼·明顿·贝多斯、沙尚克·乔希、安东·拉瓜迪亚和阿尔卡迪·奥斯特洛夫斯基合作。</p><p class="css-1hno3qs e190yofl0">该现场活动录制于 10 月 3 日，哈马斯袭击以色列之前。 </p><iframe type="youtube" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/kRJT-Fj2SoY?enablejsapi=1" class="css-xm8n1m e195f1ec0"></iframe></div></section></div></div></div><div class="css-mqgbir ea9fiz30"><div class="css-1m3z1gu e1nb91wc1"><div class="css-1gljmzf e8tkvfk0"><div class="css-1n611c3 e1mdktgm0"><div class="css-12dw4ef ekfon2k0"><div class="css-z9n3kh ej11e0o0"><figure class="css-qts40t e1197rjj0"><img alt width="1280" sizes="(min-width: 1440px) 700px, (min-width: 1280px) 50vw, (min-width: 960px) 66vw, 95vw" srcset="https://www.economist.com/img/b/256/144/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 256w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/360/202/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 360w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/384/216/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 384w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/480/270/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 480w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/600/337/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 600w, https://www.economist.com/img/b/834/469/90/media-assets/image/20231013_FLP003.jpg 834w, https://www.economis